ids0CfgTable.name: ids0CfgTable
ids0CfgTable.description: A table of operator definable parameters for each DS0

ids0CfgEntry.name: ids0CfgEntry
ids0CfgEntry.description: There is one DS0 Configure entry for each DS0 timeslot in the chassis

ids0CfgDs1Index.name: ids0CfgDs1Index
ids0CfgDs1Index.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the CSU to which this entry is applicable. The value of ds0CfgDs1Index matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ids0CfgDs0Index.name: ids0CfgDs0Index
ids0CfgDs0Index.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the timeslot of the CSU to which this entry refers.

ids0CfgDs0Id.name: ids0CfgDs0Id
ids0CfgDs0Id.description: An operator definable string useful for easy identification of a DS0 relative to the user application.

ids0CfgBlockCallType.name: ids0CfgBlockCallType
ids0CfgBlockCallType.description: An oject that defines the type of calls to be blocked by the specified DS0. A value of blockAll(5) results in all calls to this DS0 being blocked. Default = blockNone(2).

ids0CfgDs0AssignedSlot.name: ids0CfgDs0AssignedSlot
ids0CfgDs0AssignedSlot.description: Defines which slot (1 thru 16) the specified DS0 is restricted to connect with. A value of 17 indicates that this DS0 is not restricted. If a value of 0 is returned, it it indicatesthat this NAC does not support the definition of this object. Default = 17.

ids0CfgDs0AssignedChannel.name: ids0CfgDs0AssignedChannel
ids0CfgDs0AssignedChannel.description: Defines which channel of a modem the specified DS0 is restricted to connect with. A value of 33 indicates that this DS0 is not restricted. If a value of 0 is returned, it it indicatesthat this NAC does not support the definition of this object. Default = 33.

ids0CfgDs0SrvcState.name: ids0CfgDs0SrvcState
ids0CfgDs0SrvcState.description: Defines the service state of a specified DS0. This object does not apply to Rob Bit T1 operation. Default = inService(2).

ids0CfgNailUpDs0.name: ids0CfgNailUpDs0
ids0CfgNailUpDs0.description: This will put a DS0 in either a normal or a Transparent mode. Normal Mode : This is a normal ds0. Transparent Mode : This provides clear ds0 channels to pass data between the T1-PRI NAC and modems.

ids0StatTable.name: ids0StatTable
ids0StatTable.description: USR's DS0 Status table contains various timeslot status information.

ids0StatEntry.name: ids0StatEntry
ids0StatEntry.description: There is one entry in the DS0 Status table for each timeslot in the chassis.

ids0StatDs1Index.name: ids0StatDs1Index
ids0StatDs1Index.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the CSU to which this entry is applicable. The value of ds0StatDs1Index matches the value of the index for the coresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ids0StatDs0Index.name: ids0StatDs0Index
ids0StatDs0Index.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the timeslot of the CSU to which this entry refers. The value of ds0StatDs0Index matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS0 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ids0StatDs0.name: ids0StatDs0
ids0StatDs0.description: This object indicates the current status of the specified timeslot. The status values change dynamically with system operation.

ids0StatDevConnTo.name: ids0StatDevConnTo
ids0StatDevConnTo.description: This object indicates the device currently connected.

ids0StatSlotConnTo.name: ids0StatSlotConnTo
ids0StatSlotConnTo.description: This object indicates the slot of the device currently connected. Range = 0(none)-16.

ids0StatChanConnTo.name: ids0StatChanConnTo
ids0StatChanConnTo.description: This object indicates the channel of the device currently connected. Default 255.

ids0StatDs0SrvcState.name: ids0StatDs0SrvcState
ids0StatDs0SrvcState.description: This is the current service state of a DS0. This object does not apply to Rob Bit T1 operation.

ids0StatCallArrivalTime.name: ids0StatCallArrivalTime
ids0StatCallArrivalTime.description: This object indicates the call arrival time in GMT w/1 sec resolution.

ids0StatCallConnectTime.name: ids0StatCallConnectTime
ids0StatCallConnectTime.description: This object indicates the call connect time in GMT w/1 sec resolution.

ids0StatCallTerminateTime.name: ids0StatCallTerminateTime
ids0StatCallTerminateTime.description: This object indicates the call terminate time in GMT w/1 sec resolution.

ids0StatCallType.name: ids0StatCallType
ids0StatCallType.description: This object indicates the call type (analog or digital).

ids0StatCallBlockState.name: ids0StatCallBlockState
ids0StatCallBlockState.description: This object indicates current ids0 call block status.

ids0StatCallDirn.name: ids0StatCallDirn
ids0StatCallDirn.description: This object indicates the call dirn (in or out bound).

ids0CmdTable.name: ids0CmdTable
ids0CmdTable.description: The DS0 Command table contains an entry for each of the manageable timeslots in the chassis. It provides a means through which to take specific actions on one or more timeslots in the chassis.

ids0CmdEntry.name: ids0CmdEntry
ids0CmdEntry.description: There is one entry in the DS0 Command table per timeslot in the chassis.

ids0CmdDs1Index.name: ids0CmdDs1Index
ids0CmdDs1Index.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the CSU to which this entry is applicable. The value of ds0CmdDs1Index matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ids0CmdDs0Index.name: ids0CmdDs0Index
ids0CmdDs0Index.description: The index which uniquely identifies the timeslot of the specified CSU to which this entry is applicable.

ids0CmdMgtStationId.name: ids0CmdMgtStationId
ids0CmdMgtStationId.description: This object is a generic read-write variable that a Management Station (MS) can use to guarantee that the results from a given command are the results of a command issued by that specific MS. Each MS must SET a unique value to this object when doing commands and GET the value of this object together with ds0CmdReqId and ds0CmdResult to detect interference from other MSs.

ids0CmdReqId.name: ids0CmdReqId
ids0CmdReqId.description: This object contains the value of the request-id field in the SNMP PDU which invoked the current or most recent command on this DS0 entity. If the request-id is unknown or undefined, this object contains the zero value.

ids0CmdFunction.name: ids0CmdFunction
ids0CmdFunction.description: This object contains a value that identifies the command being requested.

ids0CmdForce.name: ids0CmdForce
ids0CmdForce.description: In some cases, the DS0 entity may be in a state such that certain commands could adversely affect connections. In such cases, a command request with ds0CmdForce not defined, or set to noForce will result in a warning. If the operator elects to ignore such warnings, ds0CmdForce can be set to force in a re-issued request and the command will be carried out regardless of its potentially hazzardous effects.

ids0CmdParam.name: ids0CmdParam
ids0CmdParam.description: This object contains parameters that are specific to the particular command being issued. In some cases, there will be no additional parameters required.

ids0CmdResult.name: ids0CmdResult
ids0CmdResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested command, or the value none(1) if no commands have been requested since the last reset.

ids0CmdCode.name: ids0CmdCode
ids0CmdCode.description: The value of this object upon command completion indicates a further description of what went wrong if the command was unsuccessful.

ids0BulkAccessTable.name: ids0BulkAccessTable
ids0BulkAccessTable.description: A table of parameters for each DS0 accessed in a bulk format

ids0BulkAccessEntry.name: ids0BulkAccessEntry
ids0BulkAccessEntry.description: There is one bulk DS0 access for each DS1 in the chassis

ids0BulkAccessDs1Index.name: ids0BulkAccessDs1Index
ids0BulkAccessDs1Index.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the CSU to which this entry is applicable. The value of ds0BulkAccessDs1Index matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

ids0BulkAccessStatDs0Mdm.name: ids0BulkAccessStatDs0Mdm
ids0BulkAccessStatDs0Mdm.description: This object contains all of the ids0Stat table parameters for all the DS0's on the DS1
